Sentencas: The swift advancement of the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) sector necessitates a harmony between electrode performance and commercialization cost.
Titulo: Developing abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes for high-performance and low-cost solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The economic value of elements is frequently linked to their abundance in the Earth's crust.
Titulo: Developing abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes for high-performance and low-cost solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here, we develop abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes of Ln 0.6 Sr 0.4 FeO 3-8 (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) with high abundant rare-earth metals and preferred iron metal for SOFCs.
Titulo: Developing abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes for high-performance and low-cost solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All three symmetric electrode materials display a cubic perovskite phase and excellent chemical compatibility with Gd 0.2 Ce 0.8 O 2-8 electrolyte.
Titulo: Developing abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes for high-performance and low-cost solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All three electrodes possess exceptional surface oxygen exchange ability.
Titulo: Developing abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes for high-performance and low-cost solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, single cells with La 0.6 Sr 0.4 FeO 3-8 , Pr 0.6 Sr 0.4 FeO 3-8 , and Nd 0.6 Sr 0.4 FeO 3-8 symmetric electrodes attained excellent open circuit voltages of 1.108, 1.101, and 1.097 V, respectively, as well as peak powers of 213.52, 281.12, and 254.58 mW cm -2 .
Titulo: Developing abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes for high-performance and low-cost solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results suggest that overall performance of abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes has a favorable impact on the extensive expansion of SOFCs, presenting significant potential for practical applications.
Titulo: Developing abundant rare-earth iron perovskite electrodes for high-performance and low-cost solid oxide fuel cells
